# Line endings.
#
# This working tree is shared between Windows, WSL and macOS: without explicit
# rules, each git applies its own autocrlf policy and `git status` fills up with
# phantom whole-file CRLF diffs. Rule: every text file is stored AND checked out
# with LF, on every OS (editors, dotnet, bash/zsh and PowerShell 7 all handle LF).
* text=auto eol=lf

# Windows-only scripts keep CRLF (cmd.exe requires it; safest for PowerShell 5.1)
*.ps1 text eol=crlf
*.bat text eol=crlf
*.cmd text eol=crlf

# Vendored ONLYOFFICE payloads: never inspect or convert. Critical for
# x2t/bin/macos-arm64/: the .framework Info.plist/_CodeSignature files are
# covered by the code signature -- byte-level changes would break codesign.
x2t/bin/** -text

# Binary formats (belt and braces on top of text=auto detection)
*.dll binary
*.exe binary
*.so binary
*.so.* binary
*.dylib binary
*.zip binary
*.dat binary
*.bin binary
*.wasm binary
*.cache binary
*.ttf binary
*.otf binary
*.ttc binary
*.ico binary
*.icns binary
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.pdf binary
*.docx binary
*.xlsx binary
*.pptx binary
